title: Front-End Developer, Contractor
description: Design visual and interactive web applications for small local companies and entrepreneurs. Implement the use of UX/UI interfaces to create a more interactive and modern user experience. Use the correct technologies for the application; this can include the use of CSS and Javascript frameworks such as: Twitter Bootstrap, Foundation, and AngularJS. Create quality mock-ups and prototypes on tight timelines while utilizing best W2C specification and practices. Provide website maintenance and enhancements for web applications.

title: Community Health Outreach Worker, SFUSD
description: Provide outreach to both the school and the community at large to promote the Wellness Program and its services. This outreach includes promotion of the Wellness Program to students, school staff, parents, and Community-based Organizations (CBOs). Collaborates with a team of health professionals to offer health and wellness services to students such as assessments, treatment and referrals for reproductive health, physical health, mental health, and substance use concerns. Design and develop mid to large scale events for the community and assigned location.
